Given preorder traversal of a binary search tree, construct the BST.

For example, if the given traversal is {10, 5, 1, 7, 40, 50}, then the output should be root of following tree.
     10
   /   \
  5     40
 /  \      \
1    7      50

Solution:
The trick is to set a range {min .. max} for every node. Initialize the range as {INT_MIN .. INT_MAX}. The first node will definitely be in range, so create root node. To construct the left subtree, set the range as {INT_MIN â€¦root->data}. If a values is in the range {INT_MIN .. root->data}, 
the values is part part of left subtree. To construct the right subtree, set the range as {root->data..max .. INT_MAX}.

int ind = 0;
    public TreeNode helper(int[] preorder, int lo, int hi) {
        if(ind >= preorder.length) return null;
        
        int key = preorder[ind];
        TreeNode node = null;
        if(key > lo && key < hi){
            node = new TreeNode(preorder[ind]);
            ind++;
            node.left = helper(preorder, lo, key);
            node.right = helper(preorder, key, hi);
        }
        return node;
    }
    
    public TreeNode bstFromPreorder(int[] preorder) {
        if (preorder == null)
            return null;
        return helper(preorder, Integer.MIN_VALUE, Integer.MAX_VALUE);
    }
